      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(usage): exclude untimestamped records from daily ranges",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhat problem does this PR solve?\n\n- Fixes ranged dashboard/session usage summaries so untimestamped cached transcript rows do not inflate selected-day totals or model usage.\n- Keeps all-time cache summaries intact, but forces finite date ranges to derive from timestamped transcript rows only.\n\nWhy does this matter now?\n\n- Issue #89709 reports that after v2026.5.28, Dashboard \"今日模型调用\" can show historical cumulative model usage for a selected day.\n\nWhat is the intended outcome?\n\n- A selected-day usage range only includes transcript usage rows with timestamps inside that range.\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope?\n\n- No UI layout changes, provider pricing changes, Discord changes, memory-core changes, Mattermost changes, or MCP changes.\n\nWhat does success look like?\n\n- Ranged usage summaries exclude untimestamped historical records from total tokens, message counts, tool usage, model usage, daily breakdowns, and daily model usage.\n\nWhat should reviewers focus on?\n\n- The cache-derived session summary path in `src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts` and the deterministic regression fixture in `src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts`.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nCloses #89709\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nRelated #87222\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\n- ClawSweeper marked #89709 as source-repro, queueable-fix, and fix-shape-clear.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Selected-day Dashboard/session usage ranges no longer include untimestamped historical cached transcript records in model totals.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on branch `codex/89709-daily-usage-range`, using the actual `refreshCostUsageCache` and `loadSessionCostSummaryFromCache` runtime functions with a temp `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran `node --import tsx -` with a fixture containing an untimestamped historical `openai/glm-5` assistant usage row for 1000 tokens, an out-of-range dated `gpt-5.5` row for 10 tokens, and selected-day `gpt-5.5` usage for 20 tokens, then loaded the range `2026-02-05T00:00:00.000Z` through `2026-02-05T23:59:59.999Z` from the cache.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"cacheStatus\": \"fresh\",\n  \"totalTokens\": 20,\n  \"totalCost\": 0.02,\n  \"messageCounts\": {\n    \"total\": 2,\n    \"user\": 1,\n    \"assistant\": 1,\n    \"toolCalls\": 1,\n    \"toolResults\": 0,\n    \"errors\": 0\n  },\n  \"modelUsage\": [\n    \"openai/gpt-5.5:20\"\n  ],\n  \"dailyModelUsage\": [\n    \"2026-02-05/openai/gpt-5.5:20\"\n  ],\n  \"dailyBreakdown\": [\n    {\n      \"date\": \"2026-02-05\",\n      \"tokens\": 20,\n      \"cost\": 0.02\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The ranged cache summary reports only the selected-day `gpt-5.5` usage; the untimestamped `glm-5` 1000-token historical record is absent from `totalTokens`, `messageCounts`, `modelUsage`, and `dailyModelUsage`.\n- What was not tested: I did not run a browser Dashboard session against a reporter WSL2 profile or their real provider console data.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The reporter's actual local cache was not available, so the proof uses a deterministic temp state dir that exercises the same source-proven cache aggregation path.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): The prior source path only skipped out-of-range rows when `timestamp` existed, so untimestamped cached rows could still be added to ranged `totals` and `modelUsage`.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/usage.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/usage.sessions-usage.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/usage.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/usage-render-overview.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.node.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- Updated the cached session range regression to include an untimestamped historical model usage record and assert the selected-day summary only contains the timestamped selected-day model.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\n- The same cache-derived range path could include untimestamped records in aggregate totals and `modelUsage` because timestamp filtering only rejected entries with timestamps outside the range.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\n- A focused regression test was added.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes. Date-filtered usage totals and model usage now exclude untimestamped records.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\n- Ranged usage summaries for legacy cached transcript rows without timestamps.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\n- The change is limited to finite-range cache derivation. All-time summaries still include untimestamped entries, and regression coverage exercises the exact selected-day leak shape.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\n- Maintainer review and ClawSweeper review.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\n- CI and ClawSweeper verdict.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\n- Addresses ClawSweeper's source-repro notes on #89709 for untimestamped cached usage leaking into ranged model totals.\n",
